lead_paragraph: Lulz Security, an offshoot of the Anonymous hacker group, has claimed responsibility for computer attacks on prominent government, media and law enforcement Web sites.

headline.seo: Two LulzSec Hackers Plead Guilty in Britain
headline.main: Two LulzSec Hackers Plead Guilty in Britain
headline.print_headline: Two British Men Admit Role In Series of Computer Attacks

abstract: British hackers Ryan Cleary and Jake Davis, linked to the Lulz Security group, plead guilty to several computer crimes; Lulz, an offshoot of the Anonymous group, has claimed responsibility for attacks on prominent government, media and law enforcement Web sites.
